Notes from http://charless.org/?p=283

	Github is a web-based hosting service for software development projects that use the Git revision control system.
	
	Cloud9 is a state-of-the-art IDE that runs in your browser and lives in the cloud, 
	allowing you to run, debug and 	deploy applications from anywhere, anytime.
	
	Node.js is a server-side JavaScript environment that uses an asynchronous event-driven model. 
	This allows Node.js to 	get excellent performance based on the architectures of many Internet applications.
	
	Heroku (pronounced her-OH-koo) is a cloud application platform â€“ a new way of building and deploying web apps. 
	It lets	developers spend 100% of their time on their application code, 
	not managing servers, deployment, ongoing operations, 	or scaling.
	
	In this post, I will show you how to quickly develop and deploy a web(socket) application with Javascript, 
	by using 	only a web browser, all for free.
	

